Html:
Yes I ran into this to.  It seems to be an issue between MVC 3 empty template and MVC 4 empty template, which you probably chose <br />
<br />
So what I did was just download the complete solution and added the folder and the _Layout.cshtml<br />
<br />
<br />
here is the code if you can't download the solution <br />
<pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;@ViewBag.Title&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;link href=&quot;@Url.Content(&quot;~/Content/Site.css&quot;)&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; type=&quot;text/css&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;@Url.Content(&quot;~/Scripts/jquery-1.5.1.min.js&quot;)&quot; type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;@Url.Content(&quot;~/Scripts/modernizr-1.7.min.js&quot;)&quot; type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

      &lt;script src=&quot;@Url.Content(&quot;~/Scripts/jquery.validate.unobtrusive.min.js&quot;)&quot; type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

    @RenderSection(&quot;Scripts&quot;, required: false)
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;header&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;
            ASP.NET MVC MUSIC STORE&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;ul id=&quot;navlist&quot;&gt;
            &lt;li class=&quot;first&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/&quot; id=&quot;current&quot;&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/Store/&quot;&gt;Store&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    @RenderBody()


&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>

You are also going to want to add a Scripts directory from the root as I don't think the empty template did this then add the jquery scripts.  To get them you can create a new MVC4 solution but pick Intranet as your template and it will create the script folder Shared and _ViewStart<br />
